# HubSpot API credentials for Phase 2 scripts.
#
# HubSpot deprecated Private Apps in favor of Service Keys. Use Service Keys.
#
# HOW TO GET THIS KEY:
#   1. In HubSpot, go to: Settings → Integrations → Service Keys
#      (If you land on the legacy "Create Private App" page, click
#      "Use Service Keys instead" — same result, current API.)
#   2. Click "Create" / "Add new key"
#   3. Name it: "CRM Cleanup Phase 2 — Execution"
#   4. Add the following 9 scopes (use the search box):
#        Schema scopes (for deleting property definitions):
#          - crm.schemas.contacts.read
#          - crm.schemas.contacts.write
#          - crm.schemas.companies.read
#          - crm.schemas.companies.write
#          - crm.schemas.deals.read
#          - crm.schemas.deals.write
#        Object read scopes (for the pre-deletion safety check):
#          - crm.objects.contacts.read
#          - crm.objects.companies.read
#          - crm.objects.deals.read
#   5. Generate the key and copy it immediately (HubSpot only shows it once)
#   6. Paste the key as the value below
#
# DO NOT COMMIT .env TO GIT. The .env file is gitignored.
# Rotate/delete this key after Phase 2 execution completes.

HUBSPOT_ACCESS_TOKEN=paste-your-token-here
